
Future Value Formula: 
FV = PV(1 + r)^t
FV: future value 
PV: present value 
r: "interest" (average annualized rate of return in this case)
t: time (in years)

References 

The historical average rate of return was taken from here: 
https://www.chase.com/personal/investments/learning-and-insights/article/what-is-the-average-stock-market-return

More conservative rate of return suggestion was taken from here: 
https://www.nerdwallet.com/investing/learn/average-stock-market-return

